# Cloudflare Pages response headers (F9D enforced security headers).
# app.feelflick.com is served by Cloudflare Pages (see public/_redirects), so this
# file — NOT vercel.json — is what reaches production. vercel.json mirrors these for
# the Vercel preview/deploy path.
#
# These five headers are ENFORCED (F9D) and apply to every response. The report-only
# CSP is NO LONGER set here — F9G.3 moved it to functions/_middleware.js so it can
# carry a PER-REQUEST nonce (which a static file can't do). The nonce lets Cloudflare
# auto-nonce its JavaScript-Detections inline script, clearing the last CSP report-only
# violation without `script-src 'unsafe-inline'`. See docs/cloudflare-csp-nonce-f9g3.md.
# (vercel.json keeps a static report-only CSP for the non-Cloudflare preview path,
# which has no JS Detections.)

/*
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), browsing-topics=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000
